H0.text: 200 thousand is the number closest to the estimated number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy.

H1.text: 200 million is the number closest to the estimated number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy.

H2.text: 200 billion is the number closest to the estimated number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy.

H3.text: 200 trillion is the number closest to the estimated number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy.

A4.text: The Milky Way contains between 100 and 400 billion stars and at least that many planets.
